mPccMsgHandler

public Messenger mPccMsgHandler
Handles cmd msgs coming from pcc Having one handler for all the devices allows us to catch global events and decreases resource usage. Furthermore, since the Ant chip can only take one cmd at a time, we aren't bottlenecking the cmd pipeline

handleAccessRequest

public boolean handleAccessRequest(int requestMode,
                                   Messenger msgr_ResultMessenger,
                                   AntPluginDevice.ClientInfo prospectiveClient,
                                   Bundle reqParams)
This function handles requests from a pcc to acquire a token, including interacting with the radio service search logic and sending the response back to the pcc Subclasses can override this method to replace the default processing of an access request. At the time this function is called, the service will be bound to the ARS, but no further processing of the request has occurred. After examining the request, if the subclass assumes responsibility to process the request, they should return true. Returning false resumes the default request processing.

Parameters:
requestMode -
msgr_ResultMessenger -
prospectiveClient -
reqParams -
Returns:
